	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=827><span id= >Tashanya</span></a><br><span id=notbold>13 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>However if you have some time to setup up.. you can get 3 or 4 pets out quick... Stratogy is:<br><br>Summon Orb. Use orb, Sit pet down. wait 5 min.<br>Destroy orb, Summon a new one, wield it. Wait 5 min.<br><br>Send pet in. When pet dies, Resummon with the existing orb, and destroy it. Cast a new orb while mob buisy with pet. Sit and wait. When current pet dies, use the last orb you have and hope that eithor A: Pet wins fight. or B: the time between the last cast of orb and the second pet dieing is greater than 5 min, Or C: You are bound nearby.<br><br>Eithor way you just got 3 or 4 pets out, without having to stand there for ten seconds without a pet. (or trying to time the /pet get lost). <br><br>Pet is useful. Pet is more usefull if there is a cleric casting CH on it. <br><br><br></p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
